      • getPath

        public Vector2[] getPath(Vector2 startPoint,
                         Vector2 endPoint,
                         Moving moving)
        Gets the path(if any) from a start point on the map to an end point on the map for a given moving entity.
        Parameters:
        startPoint - The grid coordinates to start on.
        endPoint - The grid coordinates to find a path to.
        moving - The moving entity that must be able to traverse the path.
        Returns:
        An array of coordinates leading from(but not including) the start point to (including) the end point.

      • processNeighbour

        public void processNeighbour(Vector2 neighbourCoord,
                             Vector2 endPoint,
                             AStarNode currentNode,
                             Moving moving)
        Updates the traversal cost of a neighbouring coordinate and adds its node to the open list. The end point node costs 0.
        Parameters:
        neighbourCoord - The coordinate of this neighbour.
        endPoint - The coordinate we're finding a path to
        currentNode - The node we came from to get to this neighbour.
        moving - The moving entity that must be able to traverse the path.
